# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Docker build-context exclusions.
#
# `COPY . .` in Dockerfile.api ignores .gitignore — it ONLY honours this file.
# Without it, secrets (.env), user PII (conversations.db) and hundreds of MB of
# data/vector/graph dirs get baked into image layers (recoverable via
# `docker history`). Everything below is either a secret, runtime state, or data
# that is mounted as a volume at runtime — none of it belongs in the image.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Version control
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Secrets / environment (keep ONLY the template)
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Python virtual environments & caches
venv/
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
.python-version

# Runtime state & user data (NEVER ship these in an image)
conversations.db
conversations.db-wal
conversations.db-shm
ingest_manifest.json
drupal_ingestion_state.json

# Large data / generated stores (mounted as volumes at runtime)
chroma_db/
neo4j_data/
downloads/
atlases_pdfs/
eval_runs/
eval_results.md
models_cache/
models--*/
venv/


# Tests & docs are not needed in the runtime image
tests/
docs/
*.md
!README.md

# IDE
.vscode/
.idea/
.claude/
